						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Personally, I prefer the thick highlights, but of course it's hard to judge my own artwork objectively. </div>
<br />Well, it's YOUR project or it isn't ?
<br />When doing graphics, it's often really hard to make choises like that. But you can't ask someone else for each piece of graphics if it's better making this pixel lighter or darker, and so on.
<br />I've had in my game a sky that looks green, and I thought it looked weird. So I changed it to blue, but then attribute clash would make the cliff before the sky look parially blue as well, and this was looking horrible. It's hard to chose, have a cliff looking blue and that doesn't look very good, or having the sky looking green. I still haven't decided definiteely, but oh well. I won't ask to everyone what the best is because it's my game so I can't ask to someone else each time I should take a decision.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
