					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can also map the jump and the bionic arm to the same button, which means that the player will have to jump first before using the bionic arm.  That's what Earthworm Jim 2 did with Jim's Snott Swing, which is like the bionic arm.  Personally, I'd think that'd be faster than toggling between the gun and bionic arm with the Select button or using the Start button (especially on an NES controller), but that may not be much of a problem depending on the level design.</div>

